# BASELINE REPRODUCTION: Erratic Whitespace and Formatting
# Validates that the lexer and parser correctly handle varied and extreme whitespace,
# including missing spaces between braces and keywords, multiple blank lines, and erratic indentation.
# The tool MUST NOT crash due to token misalignment and should parse the AST correctly.
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: Parsed identically to a cleanly formatted version.
filter{
if[field]=="value"{mutate{add_field=>{"foo"=>"bar"}}}
else{
    
    
    grok{match=>{"message"=>"%{DATA:data}"}
    
    }
}
}
